-- FACTBOX: Chrysler dissident lenders
-- 
-- Wed May 6, 2009 12:41pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/06/us-chrysler-lenderssb-idUSTRE54554H20090506

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Stairway Capital Management, Foxhill Opportunity Master Fund and Arrow Distressed Securities are among a group of Chrysler lenders who oppose the company's plan to use the bankruptcy process to quickly sell itself, according to court documents. 

 The group asked the court to keep their names unpublished, saying they feared harm to their professional reputations or even their families, but a judge ordered that the participants be revealed. The aggregate holdings of the group amount to about $295 million. The Chrysler Non-TARP Lenders, grouped in parties, are: Oppenheimer Senior Floating Rate Fund Oppenheimer Master Loan Fund LLC Stairway Capital Management II, L.P. Group G Partners LP GGCP Sequoia L.P. Schultze Master Fund Ltd. Schultze Apex Master Fund Arrow Distressed Securities Fund Foxhill Opportunity Master Fund LP The case is In re: Chrysler LLC, U.S. Bankruptcy Court, Southern District of New York, No. 09-50002. (Editing by  Andre Grenon )